body_html:
@JcmeLs Hi JcmeLs. My code worked well in tf v0.8.0. I updated the tf.pack in tf v0.8.2 to tf.stack in tf v1.2.0. It reported the same error:
OutOfRangeError (see above for traceback): FIFOQueue '_1_batch/fifo_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements (requested 1, current size 0) [[Node: batch = QueueDequeueManyV2[component_types=[DT_UINT8, DT_UINT8], timeout_ms=-1, _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0"](batch/fifo_queue, batch/n)]]

The following are all of my changes.
original code in tf v0.8.2:

new_shape = tf.pack([scale,scale])
img = tf.image.resize_images(img, new_shape[0], new_shape[1])

changed code in tf v1.2.0

new_shape = tf.stack([scale,scale])
img = tf.image.resize_images(img, [new_shape[0], new_shape[1]])

So how did you solve the '_1_batch/fifo_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements' error?
thanks.

body:
@JcmeLs  Hi JcmeLs. My code worked well in tf v0.8.0. I updated the tf.pack in tf v0.8.2 to tf.stack in tf v1.2.0. It reported the same error: 
`OutOfRangeError (see above for traceback): FIFOQueue '_1_batch/fifo_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements (requested 1, current size 0) [[Node: batch = QueueDequeueManyV2[component_types=[DT_UINT8, DT_UINT8], timeout_ms=-1, _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0"](batch/fifo_queue, batch/n)]]`

The following are all of my changes.
**original code in tf v0.8.2:**
```
new_shape = tf.pack([scale,scale])
img = tf.image.resize_images(img, new_shape[0], new_shape[1])
```

**changed code in tf v1.2.0**
```
new_shape = tf.stack([scale,scale])
img = tf.image.resize_images(img, [new_shape[0], new_shape[1]])
```

So how did you solve the  '_1_batch/fifo_queue' is closed and has insufficient elements' error?
thanks.
